@csantanapr I understand your concern, but note that the behavior is consistent; currently when you specify the `kind` flag you can pass anything you want (e.g. a `.swift` file as a NodeJS action, etc.).

If we want to change that we should probably open a different issue.

Similarly, `wsk action create -h` currently doesn't indicate any connection between extensions and kinds (our online docs do that).
